President Trump gave a speech at the Pennsylvania Convention Center in Philadelphia, where he addressed the National Electrical Contractors Association. He thanked the association for their work and praised the skill and talent of electrical contractors. He also highlighted the achievements of his administration, including the strong economy, job creation, and the renegotiation of trade deals. He emphasized his commitment to protecting American workers and businesses, and highlighted the importance of vocational education and apprenticeships. Several individuals from the industry also spoke about their experiences and the positive impact of Trump's policies on their businesses.